Preparation of glaze with Crisco is not difficult, and it can be made not only using crystalline silicon dioxide, but also with the help of other components.

Favorite compositions of glaze with crystalline silicon dioxide:

1. 20 grams of crystalline silicon dioxide;
2. 30 grams of water;
3. 10 grams of urea;
4. 10 grams of nitric acid;
5. 20 grams of silicate binder (for example, aluminum silicate).

To obtain glaze using silicon mass, you should:
1. Add water to the cooled mixer of crystalline silicon dioxide until a strong solution is formed;
2. Add urea and nitric acid and gradually stir until a thick solution is formed;
3. Add the silicate binder and gradually stir until a homogeneous mass is formed, which, when crushed, forms glaze;
4. Remove the undissolved particles of the silicon mass by crushing.
This glaze will be transparent and translucent.

